A vintage 1980s computer repair shop scene with warm amber lighting, featuring a Windows PC tower cracked open on a wooden workbench, its internal components exposed like a mechanical autopsy. Scattered around are floppy disks, tangled cables, and a worn spiral notebook with handwritten notes. A magnifying glass hovers over a single tiny configuration file card, suggesting detective work. The scene has the aesthetic of aged Kodachrome photography with subtle grain, muted yellows and browns, and the nostalgic atmosphere of early computing troubleshooting. Tools like screwdrivers and anti-static wrist straps add authenticity. A small desk lamp casts dramatic shadows across the cluttered workspace.
